Package: ifc
Title: International Fixed Calendar Date Class
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R:
    person("Kiernan", "Nicholls", email = "k5cents@gmail.com",
           role = c("aut", "cre", "cph"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-9229-7897"))
Description: Implements the International Fixed Calendar (IFC) as a proper
    S3 vector class built on the vctrs framework. The IFC divides each year
    into 13 months of exactly 28 days, with a Year Day appended at year's end
    (and a Leap Day after IFC June 28 in leap years). Because each month always
    starts on Sunday and ends on Saturday, the day-of-week for any IFC date
    is fully deterministic from the day-of-month number. Provides constructors,
    accessors, arithmetic, formatting, and full tibble/pillar integration.
